OL,3,CHow female gorillas find their next
OL,4,Cfriendship group
OL,6,FSocialising in a new group can be
OL,7,Fnerve-wrecking, and it is always nice
OL,8,Fif you recognise someone in a social
OL,9,Fsituation.
OL,11,FNew research has found that female
OL,12,Fgorillas may feel the same in a social
OL,13,Fsituation.
OL,15,FResearchers from the University of
OL,16,FZurich and the Dian Fossey Gorilla
OL,17,FFund revealed that when transitioning
OL,18,Fto a new social group, female gorillas
OL,19,Ftend to seek out a troop that includes
OL,20,Ffemales they have previously lived
OL,21,Fwith.
